rich_text.text:
I had a similar experience getting off the birth control pill. So have thousands of other women. 

I’ve never been anti-birth control + it can be a life changing medication for some. However, it does have serious side effects including increased risk of depression & suicide.

When women talk to their doctors about these symptoms, doctors never suggest getting off of the pill or trying alternative, non-hormonal birth control. They typically just prescribe an additional psychiatric medication + put women on a pharmaceutical cocktail.
